                             Content for this page

                        NINDS Website Privacy Statement

   Get Web page suited for printing
   Email this to a friend or colleague

   This policy establishes how NINDS will use information we gather about
   you from your visit to our website. The privacy of our customers is of
   utmost importance to NINDS.

   If you visit an NINDS site...

   List bullet to read or download information: We may collect and store
   non-personal information for statistical purposes. For example, we may
   count the number of visitors to the different sections of our site to
   help us make them more useful to visitors.

   List bullet to send us an E-mail: By sending us an electronic mail
   message, you may be sending us personal information (e.g., name,
   address, E-mail address). We may store the names, addresses, and other
   information you provide in order to respond to the request or to
   otherwise resolve the subject matter of your E-mail. This information
   is never used for any other purpose than to respond to your request.

   List bullet to fill out a form: Some of our pages use forms to collect
   specific information in order to fulfill a request for information or
   materials. Other information which may be collected through feedback
   forms or other means enables us to determine a visitor's interests,
   with the goal of providing better service to those who visit our site.

   We want to be very clear: regardless of the information being
   transmitted to NINDS, we will protect all such information consistent
   with applicable law.

   To return to the page you were previously on, use your browser's back
   button.

   Reviewed July 1, 2001
